[2026-03-03T13:30:39.859Z] REQUEST: {"requestId":"req-1772544639859-zllbhok8u","timestamp":"2026-03-03T13:30:39.859Z","method":"POST","url":"/api/sessions","userAgent":"Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/145.0.0.0 Safari/537.36 Edg/145.0.0.0","ip":"::1","contentType":"application/json","contentLength":"3845","headers":{"authorization":"Bearer [TOKEN_PRESENT]","x-forwarded-for":"None","x-real-ip":"None"},"body":{"name":"ISO 27001:2022 Management Review Meeting","date":"2026-03-03T13:26:00.000Z","time":"15:26","department":"Tax","questions":[{"id":"1","text":"According to ISO/IEC 27001:2022 Clause 9.3, which of the following is a mandatory input to the information security management system (ISMS) management review?\n\nHint: Think about what ensures continuity and accountability in the ISMS improvement cycle.","options":["Results of penetration testing conducted by external vendors","Feedback from customers regarding service level agreements","Status of actions from previous management reviews","Budget forecasts for next fiscal year's IT infrastructure  "],"correctAnswer":2,"type":"multiple-choice","correctAnswerReason":"Clause 9.3(a) explicitly requires that management reviews consider \"the status of actions from previous management reviews\" to ensure follow-through on decisions and drive continual improvement. While options A, B, and D may provide valuable context, they are not mandated inputs under the standard. Penetration test results may feed into \"results of risk assessments\" (9.3.c), customer feedback may relate to \"feedback from interested parties\" (9.3.d), and budget forecasts support resource planning—but only the status of prior actions is a standalone, required input. For audit evidence, document how each mandatory input was addressed in review minutes."},{"id":"1772544432705","text":"Which of the following is a required output of an ISO 27001:2022 management review, as specified in Clause 9.3?\n\nHint: Management reviews focus on strategic direction and ISMS effectiveness—not operational details.","options":["Updated information security policy signed by the CEO","Decisions related to continual improvement opportunities","Detailed technical configuration standards for firewalls","List of employees who completed security awareness training  "],"correctAnswer":1,"type":"multiple-choice","correctAnswerReason":"Clause 9.3(b) mandates that management review outputs include \"decisions related to continual improvement opportunities\" alongside changes to the ISMS and resource needs. Option A may result from a review but isn't a required output format; the policy may be reaffirmed without re-signing. Option C is too tactical and belongs in implementation procedures, not executive review outputs. Option D is an operational metric that may inform the review (as input 9.3.g) but isn't a required output. Auditors should verify that review minutes explicitly capture decisions on improvement opportunities to demonstrate compliance with Clause 9.3."},{"id":"1772544511782","text":"Under ISO/IEC 27001:2022, how frequently must top management conduct ISMS management reviews?\n\nHint: The standard emphasizes flexibility for organizational context while ensuring minimum rigor.","options":["At least once per calendar year, regardless of circumstances","At planned intervals, but no less frequently than annually","Only after a major security incident or external audit finding","Quarterly, aligned with financial reporting cycles  "],"correctAnswer":1,"type":"multiple-choice","correctAnswerReason":"Clause 9.3 states management reviews shall be conducted \"at planned intervals\"—allowing organizations to align with business cycles—but adds the critical constraint \"but no less frequently than once a year.\" This balances adaptability with assurance. Option A is too rigid (ignores \"planned intervals\"); Option C is reactive and non-compliant if no annual review occurs; Option D may be good practice but isn't mandated. For audit readiness, document the planned review schedule in your ISMS procedures and retain evidence (agendas, minutes, action logs) for each review to demonstrate adherence to both timing and content requirements."}],"createdBy":"admin@bdo.co.zw","isActive":false},"query":{},"params":{}}
